songs.description: This song became very important to me after my neighbor passed away. I'd listen to it in my car over and over hit hard by the part "can I believe in a me before I knew you beautifully".

The original, Modern Baseball version is also great: <https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BKpM-rswtyM>

[](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BKpM-rswtyM)One of my favs to listen to while driving from CA to ID where I was moving to.
Love belting out the "Family" and "Break you right back".
Since moving to a place with trees been obsessed with this band.
Another good moody drive song. Also reminds me of my relationship beginnings.
Things have changed greatly for me and it's hard sometimes.
Listened to this many many times, while walking, running, driving, since beginning my obsession with this band in 2022.
I'm not much of a music artist myself, but my own music development has meant loads to me. Writing and recording my own simple tunes has helped process stuff changing in my life and my emotions.
This band reminds me of driving in LA at night. This song is just so calming and nostalgic, even while LA wasn't far away from me.
Another one of those songs always on my rotation. There's no particular meaning for me other than something to sing kinda angry to.
